âœ… 6. Technical Specification â€“ Unit Conversion, Pricing, and Invoicing
6.1 Business Logic: Unit Conversion & Pricing
ğŸ”· Core Logic:
Order pricing is determined based on whether the selected unit matches the productâ€™s base unit or requires conversion using alternate units.
________________________________________
ğŸŸ© Case 1: Matching Unit Type
No conversion required.
 Formula:
totalAmount = order.quantity Ã— product.ratePerUnit

________________________________________
ğŸŸ¨ Case 2: Alternate Unit Conversion
If the productâ€™s unit is squareMeter or squareFeet and the order is in NOS, conversion applies.
Formula:
pricePerUnit = product.alternateUnits.numberOfUnits / product.alternateUnits.numberOfItems
convertedRate = product.ratePerUnit Ã— pricePerUnit
totalAmount = convertedRate Ã— order.quantity

Example:
product.unitType = "squareFeet"
product.alternateUnits = { numberOfItems: 150, numberOfUnits: 100 }
product.ratePerUnit = 100
order.unitType = "NOS"
order.quantity = 20

â†’ pricePerUnit = 100 / 150 = 0.6667
â†’ convertedRate = 100 Ã— 0.6667 = 66.67
â†’ totalAmount = 66.67 Ã— 20 = â‚¹1333.4

________________________________________
ğŸŸ¥ Case 3: Invalid Unit Type
Reject if:
â—	Unit type mismatches and no alternateUnits are defined

â—	Product unit is NOS but order unit isnâ€™t NOS

________________________________________
âš ï¸ Validation Rules
â—	If product.unitType === 'NOS', order must also be in NOS

â—	If unit is squareMeter or squareFeet, allow ordering in NOS, squareMeter, or squareFeet only if alternateUnits are defined

________________________________________
6.2 Backend Module Integration
â—	Validate unit compatibility during order creation/update

â—	Apply relevant pricing logic

â—	Save totalAmount, discountedAmount

â—	Invoice is generated based on calculated total

